Sure, here are several example sentences in Serbian that use the word "sveže" in different forms and positions, with translations in English in parentheses:

1. *Sveže* sam ispekla hleb. (I just baked fresh bread.)
2. Nemoj da jedes pokvarenu hranu, već samo *sveže*. (Don't eat spoiled food, only fresh.)
3. Da li imate *svežu* ribu danas? (Do you have fresh fish today?)
4. Možemo li kupiti *sveže* voće na pijaci? (Can we buy fresh fruit at the market?)
5. Oni su *sveži* u grad stigli. (They just arrived fresh in the city.)
6. Ja obično pijem *sveže* ceđen sok ujutru. (I usually drink fresh squeezed juice in the morning.)
7. Moramo da održimo *svežu* hranu u frižideru. (We need to keep fresh food in the fridge.)
8. *Svežim* vazduhom mogu da poboljšam svoje raspoloženje. (Fresh air can improve my mood.)
9. Taman sam doručkovao, iako bih radije jeo *sveže* pecivo. (I just had breakfast, although I would rather eat fresh pastry.)
10. Danas je *sveže* i sunčano, idealno za izlet. (Today is fresh and sunny, perfect for a trip.)